==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interventor
<hw>In`ter*ven"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.: cf. F.
<ets>interventeur</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who intervenes; a mediator;
especially <fld>(Eccles. Hist.)</fld>, a person designated by a church
to reconcile parties, and unite them in the choice of officers.</def>
<rj><au>Coleman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

